column5: Is the End of Main still open? We use to put our boat in there but I heard that it might be closed. Does anybody know for sure? Thanks, Katch

You talking about way north by the bridge?? I think it should be open with the high water but it can be swampy. We always used the city park but it was too low last year so we used Stu/Cats on the Red a few days. Good luck. Thanks for the remarks on the other thread. Todd "Tell the cook this is low-grade dog food. This steak still has marks where the jockey was hittin' it."
The end of main launch is closed due to a land use dispute.Use the launch at Stu's Cats on the Red in Lockport or the launch in Selkirk Park.See you on the water:).
This is all I know about ithttp://looneybeaver.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4886

Still closed, sign posted at Clandeboye rd and breezy point road. Try willow springs campground a lot closer to the mouth than Selkirk Park. Willow springs is about halfway between end of main and clandeboye road. Nothing has changed since the following was posted http://manitobaanglers.com/fly/News/article/sid=40.html You could put in at chesleys off #9 and fish your way down as the greenbacks do make their way up netley creek.
